cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the impact of filter bubbles on online communities, which involves social interactions and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses agent-based simulation, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper discusses personalisation algorithms, which can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper also touches upon the human-computer interaction aspect of online communities, which can be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
